{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The of using microlensing for probing the structure of the outflowing gas in BAL quasars has been proposed very early, but yet applied to a limited number of systems (e.g.",
    "Hutsemékers 1993 Hutsemékers, 1994;; Lewis et al. 1998; Chelouche 2005).",
    "The best-studied system is H1413+117, a.k.a. the cloverleaf.",
    "The main insights on the geometry of the outflow come from the decomposition of the line profiles using the MmD decomposition (see Sect. 3.2.2).",
    "The analysis of this system (Hutsemékers et al. 2010; O'Dowd et al. 2015) reveals (a) a nearly black absorption of C IV in the microlensed flux, and unveils the underlying line emission in the non microlensed component; (b) an onset velocity of the absorption of about 1500 km s -1 for C IV and a larger velocity onset of Si IV and Al III; (c) part of the C IV emission is reabsorbed over a small wavelength range."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Hutsemékers 1993 Hutsemékers, 1994;; Lewis et al. 1998; Chelouche 2005).",
